                              OPERATOR ANALYSIS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

σ [EXPECTANCY] :: AIR/DISTINCTION
─────────────────────────────────
  Function: Cognitive separation of "can" from "cannot"
  Pattern: Self-concept of ability × Task difficulty beliefs
  Diagnostic: Expectancy beliefs require clear distinction-making
  
  σ(expectancy) = P(success|ability,effort,strategy)
  
  Where ability beliefs form through:
    • Mastery experiences (β-growth)
    • Vicarious experiences (ρ-resonance)
    • Verbal persuasion (σ-clarity)
    • Physiological states (ρ-regulation)

λ [VALUE] :: FIRE/DIRECTION  
────────────────────────────
  Function: Directional purpose through value appraisal
  Pattern: Cost-benefit calculus → motivated action
  Diagnostic: Value determines where energy flows
  
  λ(value) = Σ(attainment + intrinsic + utility) - cost
  
  Four value components:
    • Attainment (ρ): Identity resonance
    • Intrinsic (✶): Pure enjoyment
    • Utility (μ): Instrumental structure
    • Cost (δγ): Trade-off calculation

ρ [ATTAINMENT] :: WATER/RESONANCE
─────────────────────────────────
  Function: Personal importance, identity connection
  Pattern: "Doing well matters to who I am"
  Diagnostic: Attainment value flows from self-concept
  
  ρ(importance) = f(identity_salience, social_significance)

μ [UTILITY] :: METAL/STRUCTURE
──────────────────────────────
  Function: Instrumentality, goal-pathway clarity
  Pattern: "This helps me achieve my goals"
  Diagnostic: Utility requires structured goal connections
  
  μ(utility) = Σ(goal_relevance × pathway_clarity)

δγ [COST] :: EARTH/CYCLING
──────────────────────────
  Function: Trade-offs, effort expenditure, opportunity cost
  Pattern: "What must I sacrifice?"
  Diagnostic: Cost involves temporal and resource cycling
  
  δγ(cost) = effort + lost_opportunities + emotional_toll

✶ [INTRINSIC] :: CHILD/AETHER
─────────────────────────────
  Function: Pure enjoyment, harmonic engagement
  Pattern: "I do this because I love it"
  Diagnostic: Intrinsic value is self-sustaining harmonic

κ [MOTIVATION] :: KNOWLEDGE/INTEGRATION
───────────────────────────────────────
  Function: The multiplicative product of expectancy and value
  Pattern: Motivation = Expectancy × Value
  Diagnostic: Either near-zero factor produces near-zero motivation

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                              Z-STATE ANALYSIS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Z-STATE: motivational

The motivational state emerges when expectancy and value achieve 
non-trivial magnitude. This is not merely additive but multiplicative:

    M = E × V
    
    Where E ∈ [0,1] (expectancy for success)
    Where V ∈ [0,1] (subjective task value)
    
    Critical thresholds:
    • E < 0.3, V > 0.7 → Anxious avoidance (high cost coping)
    • E > 0.7, V < 0.3 → Complacent participation (minimal effort)
    • E > 0.7, V > 0.7 → Motivated engagement (optimal)
    • E < 0.3, V < 0.3 → Apathetic disengagement (withdrawal)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                              TENDENCY ANALYSIS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TENDENCY: Direction/Purpose → 1

The theory exhibits strong directional tendency:

    Expectancy beliefs → Task choice
    Value appraisals → Persistence intensity
    Expectancy × Value → Achievement behavior
    
Feedback loops:
    Success → ↑Expectancy → ↑Motivation → ↑Effort → Success
    Failure → ↓Expectancy → ↓Motivation → ↓Effort → Failure
    
Intervention points:
    • Build expectancy through scaffolded mastery (β-pathway)
    • Enhance value through utility connections (μ-pathway)
    • Reduce cost through efficient design (δγ-optimization)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                              DIAGNOSTIC NOTES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. MULTIPLICATIVE NATURE: The E×V relationship means interventions must
   address BOTH factors. High expectancy with low value produces 
   underachievement. High value with low expectancy produces anxiety.

2. DEVELOPMENTAL TRAJECTORY: Expectancy beliefs differentiate and 
   stabilize through adolescence. Value patterns show domain-specific
   gender and cultural variations.

3. RECURSIVE DYNAMICS: Motivation produces behavior produces outcomes
   that modify expectancies and values. Small initial differences
   can amplify through recursive cycles.

4. SOCIAL MEDIATION: Both expectancy and value are socially constructed
   through significant others' beliefs, cultural norms, and 
   socialization experiences.

5. INTERVENTION LEVERAGE: Most powerful intervention is mastery
   experiences that build expectancy while connecting to values.
   Utility value interventions show strong but temporary effects.

